### Phase 4 — App Service end-to-end smoke test
###
### Hits the full submission lifecycle:
###   register/login on auth-service → list problems → submit → poll → list → stats
###
### Prerequisites:
###   - make app-db-up        (MongoDB for app_db)
###   - make execution-db-up  (Postgres for execution_db)
###   - make judge0-tunnel    (Judge0 reachable on localhost:2358)
###   - auth-service running on :8080
###   - execution-service running on :8081 / gRPC :9091
###   - app-service running on :8082
###   - make app-seed         (seed sample problems)
###
### App Service trusts the X-User-Id header — gateway sets this in Phase 5.
### For now we set it manually using the userId returned by /auth/me.

### 1. Register a fresh user (idempotent if already registered → expect 409, then login)
POST {{authUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "phase4tester@example.com",
  "username": "phase4tester",
  "password": "supersecret123"
}

> {%
    if (response.status === 201) {
      client.global.set("accessToken", response.body.accessToken);
      client.global.set("refreshToken", response.body.refreshToken);
    }
%}

### 2. Login (works whether or not register just happened)
POST {{authUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "emailOrUsername": "phase4tester@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("accessToken", response.body.accessToken);
    client.global.set("refreshToken", response.body.refreshToken);
%}

### 3. /auth/me — capture userId for the X-User-Id header
GET {{authUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

> {%
    client.global.set("userId", response.body.id);
%}

### 4. List problems → 200 with seeded data
GET {{appUrl}}/api/v1/problems

> {%
    client.global.set("problemId", response.body[0].id);
    client.global.set("problemSlug", response.body[0].slug);
%}

### 5. Get problem detail
GET {{appUrl}}/api/v1/problems/{{problemSlug}}

### 6. List languages (proxied to Execution Service via gRPC)
GET {{appUrl}}/api/v1/languages

### 7. Submit Python "hello world" → 202 with submissionId
POST {{appUrl}}/api/v1/submissions
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "problemId": "{{problemId}}",
  "languageId": 71,
  "sourceCode": "print('Hello from Phase 4 submission')",
  "customStdin": null
}

> {%
    client.global.set("submissionId", response.body.submissionId);
%}

### 8. Poll submission — repeats this until latestStatus is terminal
###    (Run a few times; Judge0 turn-around is usually 1-3s)
GET {{appUrl}}/api/v1/submissions/{{submissionId}}
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### 9. List my submissions (paginated, newest first)
GET {{appUrl}}/api/v1/submissions?page=0&size=20
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### 10. List my submissions for this problem only
GET {{appUrl}}/api/v1/submissions?problemId={{problemId}}
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### 11. Stats — should reflect the completed submission(s)
GET {{appUrl}}/api/v1/users/me/stats
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### 12. Playground submission (no problemId)
POST {{appUrl}}/api/v1/submissions
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "problemId": null,
  "languageId": 71,
  "sourceCode": "import sys\nfor line in sys.stdin: print(line.strip().upper())",
  "customStdin": "hello\nworld"
}

### 13. Missing X-User-Id header → 401
POST {{appUrl}}/api/v1/submissions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "languageId": 71,
  "sourceCode": "print('no auth')"
}

### 14. Unsupported language for problem → 400
POST {{appUrl}}/api/v1/submissions
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "problemId": "{{problemId}}",
  "languageId": 99999,
  "sourceCode": "x"
}

### 15. Health
GET {{appUrl}}/actuator/health
